                                                                                                                                     NATION BRIEFS

                   
	Mumbai, Jan. 22: A man from Bengal who attacked young women on Mumbais streets, slashing them in the chest and jabbing them with an injection needle, has been arrested after his last victim remembered his face.
     Kakun Sheikh, a 22-year-old migrant labourer, has confessed only to last weekends two attacks but police say he may well be the mystery man who had earlier slashed six women in July 2006.
     In each of the eight assaults, the victims had said the attacker carried a knife in one hand and a needle and syringe in the other, and chose a deserted spot to strike. All of them were slashed in the chest and needed hospital treatment but only the last was also pricked with a needle. 
     
	Sheikh was arrested yesterday from his home in the Marol Pipeline slums where he lives with his wife. He has been sent to police custody till tomorrow. Officers said the accused could be mentally unbalanced. 
         
	New Delhi (PTI): Spanish authorities have forwarded to India names of two persons, including one whose passport is fake, in a case involving the arrest of 14 persons for allegedly plotting terror attacks in Spain. In the first official communication from Madrid since Saturdays arrests, the names of the two  claimed to be from Hyderabad and Mumbai  were sent to Indian officials, sources said. 
         
	New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court has upheld the sacking of a constable who barged into a womans house in a drunken state for sexual favours. It slammed Andhra Pradesh High Court for reinstating him.
         
	New Delhi (PTI): A court has ordered attachment of the Iranian embassys movable property for its alleged failure to comply with a directive to compensate an abruptly dismissed employee. Ashraf Hasnain Rizvi was dismissed in 2002.
         
	Yamunanagar (PTI): A schoolbus ran over a five-year-old girl and injured another at the school in Haryana on Tuesday. Parents and residents blocked roads and threw stones at police, prompting a lathi-charge.
                                                           
